snippet: South Korea’s Inbee Park shot a 10-under-par 62 to take a three-stroke lead in the L.P.G.A. Taiwan Championship, her first event since regaining the No. 1 spot in the world on Monday.
abstract: Inbee Park of South Korea takes second-round lead in LPGA Taiwan Championship; other golf news noted.
lead_paragraph: South Korea’s Inbee Park shot a 10-under-par 62 to take a three-stroke lead in the L.P.G.A. Taiwan Championship, her first event since regaining the No. 1 spot in the world on Monday.
